CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper January 24, 1970, pg. 1, reads: "Still On Strike - Wilkinsburg refuse workers remained adamant, in their refusal to pick up garbage that has been stacked on the streets of that Borough since the week before Christmas. Currently embroiled in a salary dispute with Borough officials, the men recently rejected an offer to contract with the Borough as a private concern, and instead exercised their right to dissent, by picketing the Wilkinsburg Sanitation Department."
TitMainTitle: Wilkinsburg Sanitation Department workers picketing for higher wages and benefits in street, Wilkinsburg
